The Lagos State Government has given two weeks ultimatum to some occupants of the old Jankara market site. The Commissioner for Physical Planning and Urban Development, Dr Idris Salako, gave the ultimatum during an assessment tour of Lagos Island on Monday. Salako said that the Jankara market had been earmarked for modern development, in line with the government’s plan to regenerate Lagos Island. He said that the Ministry of Physical Planning had served all occupants notices to leave the premises as the government renewal plan for Lagos Island would commence. The commissioner said that the clearing of the market was in agreement with the State Government agenda for the total redevelopment of Lagos Island. ALSO READ: Town planners call for new master plan for Kwara State Doctors reject new minimum wage in Lagos State Lagos govt charges women on implementation of state’s agenda Lagos-Badagry Expressway: Lawmaker sends SoS to FG FG did not reject our offer to repair federal roads linking… He said that the redevelopment of the area would usher in infrastructure renewal as the people should expect modern health centre, recreational and road infrastructure, among others. Salako urged the auto mechanics, traders and occupants of illegal settlement on Adeniji Adele street to vacate before Jan. 24. He also directed the sealing of distressed buildings and schools built without planning permission in the area. Salako said that it was imperative for the government to do the needful to avert danger to life and property. He said that the government would continue to maintain its zero-tolerance policy on illegal building construction. While monitoring sites at the coastal and regional road in Oniru and Lekki axis of the state, Salako directed the removal of structures on the alignment of the regional road. (NAN) SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER